DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       Use  _s_._m_a_s_k  to filter a sites list with a raster mask.  The raster can
       be any available raster.  Sites are filtered first by the region,  then
       by  whether the site falls in a cell with a non-NULL value.  The region
       used for filtering is the current region by default.  However, the user
       may  specify  that  the  raster  mask's region be used instead.  If the
       raster mask's region is used, both it's extents and resolution are used
       in the filtering process.


       Upon  succesful  completion,  _s_._m_a_s_k will print out the total number of
       sites examined and the number of sites output.

